title: Why The $2 Million Karlmann King Is The World’s Most Expensive SUV
text: The Karlmann King is a $2 million bulletproof SUV cut like a diamond and built around a Ford F-550.  Weighing over 13,000 pounds and featuring the most extravagant interior features available, the multimillion-dollar bulletproof Karlmann King is the most expensive SUV customers can buy.

title: Genesis Mint Concept at the New York Auto Show
text: The Genesis Mint is a concept car for an urban EV with a far-out design and super fast charging.  It's certainly a "unique" design, but we dig those crazy butterfly doors.

title: Uber To Sell Minority Stake Of Its Autonomous Vehicle Unit To Japanese Consortium
